column4: US STOCKS-Nasdaq falls 1 pct as Micron  Intel weigh
column5: June 26 The Nasdaq Composite fell 1 percent in afternoon trading on Friday after weak forecast from Micron Technology dragged down chipmakers including Intel.

column4: Ex-Qualcomm exec gets one-and-a-half years in prison for insider trades
column5: A former high-ranking executive at semiconductor maker Qualcomm Inc was sentenced on Friday to a year and a half in prison and fined $500 000 for masterminding a three-year insider trading scheme.
